headers.subject: [tosdr:2827] Interest on feature that allows users to express their dislike/like of a particular terms of service

html:
Is there any interest on adding a feature that allows users to express their dislike/like of a particular terms of service? I think if many people voted against (or in favor) of  a particular terms of it could send a powerful message to the organization hosting the site. In the screenshot I am proposing these as something to vote on the overall terms of service. But perhaps it could be something for each particular issue. The implementation for this is fairly easy. The "biggest problem" is the backend, which is also really simple, but would require hosting and maintenance. I was thinking that perhaps a good alternative would be using Firebase or perhaps something like deployd and then just run deployd on a free Heroku instance. The backend would be so light that I think even that should be able to take the load. What are your thoughts?

Thanks!


--

subject: Interest on feature that allows users to express their dislike/like of a particular terms of service
text:
Is there any interest on adding a feature that allows users to express 
their dislike/like of a particular terms of service? I think if many people 
voted against (or in favor) of  a particular terms of it could send a 
powerful message to the organization hosting the site. In the screenshot I 
am proposing these as something to vote on the overall terms of service. 
But perhaps it could be something for each particular issue. The 
implementation for this is fairly easy. The "biggest problem" is the 
backend, which is also really simple, but would require hosting and 
maintenance. I was thinking that perhaps a good alternative would be using 
Firebase <https://www.firebase.com/> or perhaps something like deployd<http://deployd.com/>and then just run deployd on a free Heroku instance. The backend would be 
so light that I think even that should be able to take the load. What are 
your thoughts?

Thanks!


--
